The newly elected national chairman of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Senator Abdullahi Adamu, and his deputy (North), Senator Abubakar Kyari, have formally resigned their membership of the Senate. Before their emergence as APC leaders, both Adamu and Kyari represented Nasarawa West and Borno North senatorial districts of Nasarawa and Borno States respectively. Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, read out the duo’s letters of resignation at the commencement of Senate plenary on Tuesday morning. This is also as Lawan announced the invitation of the Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo, inviting members of the Senate APC Causus to Iftar this Tuesday evening at his official residence, Aguda House. Details Later…